{
  "message": "chore(conformance): refresh snapshot artifacts after scanf parity overhaul\n\nRegenerates the eight v1 conformance artifacts to reflect the new\nbehavior introduced by 54df9ea1 (scanf multi-arg + length-modifier\nparity, %p NULL handling, dynamic fd fixtures, regex contract matching)\nand 8dbd2164 (deterministic crash exit code).\n\n- conformance_matrix.v1.json \u2014 new pass/fail rows for every previously\n  skipped sscanf case (l/ll/llu/llx/lld/multiple/z/j/t/Lf/eof_ws_only/\n  u_max/d_overflow/d_underflow/hd/hhd/u/hu/i_overflow/x_large/o_large/\n  e_basic/f_positive_exp/f_E_exponent/f_exponent), plus refreshed\n  printf %p / strict snprintf rows.\n- errno_edge_report.v1.json \u2014 full re-run of the errno edge sweep with\n  the new dynamic-fd fixture coverage (close/lseek/read/write).\n- posix_obligation_matrix.v1.json \u2014 minor obligation tally updates.\n- fixture_unit_tests.v1.json \u2014 adds the new sscanf length-modifier and\n  printf %p unit-test rows.\n- runtime_env_inventory.v1.json, fixture_pipeline.v1.json,\n  per_symbol_fixture_tests.v1.json, conformance_coverage_snapshot.v1.json\n  \u2014 generated_at + line-number bumps to keep the inventory fresh.\n\nThese files are produced by the harness's own snapshot regeneration; no\nmanual edits.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>",
